od = Octal Dump
It shows raw data from a file â€” like the binary, hexadecimal, octal, or ASCII values.

$ od file.txt

--------------------------------------------
Option		What it does
--------------------------------------------
-c		Show characters (ASCII)
-x		Show hexadecimal output
-d		Show decimal output
-b		Show binary (octal) output
-A x		Address base (e.g. x = hex)
--------------------------------------------

Why Use od?

Debugging binary files
Seeing hidden characters
Understanding file encoding

wc - word count

$ man wc

nl - number lines of file

$ nl file
